body:
@dgquintas This still happens on branch `v1.0.x`. For some reason, though, `GRPC_TRACE` isn't working for me on that branch. Also, the client fails differently. I get an unavailable status code and the status details are:

```
{"created":"@1469740136.839567000","description":"EOF","file":"src/core/lib/iomgr/tcp_posix.c","file_line":235,"grpc_status":14}
```

@crclark yes, and I know why: at https://github.com/grpc/grpc/blob/master/src/core/lib/surface/call.c#L1412 , `effective_compression_level` is not initialized, and the following logic is such that it can remain so when there's no specification of the compression level from the channel or the call.

The fix is simply initializing `effective_compression_level` to `GRPC_COMPRESS_LEVEL_NONE`. I'm improving the tests to actually catch this error, on top of creating a PR with the fix in a matter of minutes. But just in case you wanted to quickly fix it.

Thanks for the report. This is "one of those things" and it would have been unfortunate if it'd made it into the 1.0 release :)

